I don‚Äôt think I need to give much of an intro for the prolific Shonda Rhimes. She is the creator of one of the most successful tv shows, Grey‚Äôs Anatomy (my fave!). .
This quote is from Year of Yes, and I thought it was especially poignant for entrepreneurs. There is so much advice out there about how to brand your business, how to optimize your Instagram, how to do this, how to do that. But deep down, you have to do what feels right and true to you. Otherwise, your creative work will start to become your everyday grind...which was exactly what you were trying to get away from by starting a side hustle or your own business.
.
Now, listening to your inner voice is easier said than done. Often times our inner voice tends to parrots back what we see and hear from others. You have to really pay attention and get in tune with yourself to figure out what you need and want. Without doing so, how can you achieve goals that are in sync with YOU, instead of somebody else?
.
